        "title": "feat(mobile): D-1+D-2 — hamburger nav + viewport-responsive layout",
        "body": "## Mobile Responsiveness\n\n### D-1 — Mobile navigation\n- Nav was hidden with display:none below 900px, leaving no way to navigate\n- Hamburger button + slide-in overlay drawer were already wired in `app-render.ts`; completed the implementation:\n  - **Esc key** now closes nav drawer (`globalKeydownHandler` in `app.ts`)\n  - Nav item tap targets bumped to **min-height: 44px + padding: 10px 16px** inside drawer at ≤1100px breakpoint (was 40px / 0 12px)\n- Backdrop tap-to-close and link-click-close were already in place\n\n### D-2 — Viewport-relative sizing\n- Added `@media (max-width: 768px)` block to `workboard.css`:\n  - `scroll-snap-type: x mandatory` (≤860px block used `proximity`)\n  - Column min-width: `min(260px, 82vw)` / compact `min(240px, 82vw)` / comfortable `min(280px, 82vw)`\n  - `grid-auto-columns` uses same clamp ensuring no overflow on any phone\n- Existing ≤860px tablet rule (`minmax(282px, 84vw)`) left intact\n- Fixed widths audited and left intentionally: data-table columns, attachment thumbnails, tooltips/popovers\n\n---\nPart of UI/UX Enhancement Sprint 2.",
